  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@Maaark I had a look right now, I can see the collapsible option seems not to work in your case. Could you try to first update instantsearch.js to the latest version? Your are using an old version (1.6.x), we are at 1.8.x.\n\nThen if it's still not working I would advise you to try to reproduce the bug in a isolated simple webpage first, it will help you understand what can go wrong.\n\n> And is it possible to make the collapsable functionality work with predefined window width limits? So for example we want to be the refinement lists only collapsable when the window width is < 768px?\n\nOnce the collapsible option is working in a simple webpage, you should try using our predefined CSS classes to apply some CSS media queries on top of them so that the widget are collapsed only based on the viewport.\n\nSee our CSS file (https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/instantsearch.js/1/instantsearch.css):\n\n``` css\n.ais-root__collapsible .ais-header {\n  cursor: pointer;\n}\n\n.ais-root__collapsed .ais-body, .ais-root__collapsed .ais-footer {\n  display: none;\n}\n```\n",
    "created_at": "2016-09-05T07:12:13Z",
